Class ProcessedRecord

java.lang.Object
jeroenfl.csvprocessor.model.ProcessedRecord
public class ProcessedRecord extends Object
Immutable representation of a processed CSV record.

This class encapsulates the result of processing a single CSV row, including the composite key generated from multiple CSV columns, the processed data fields, and metadata about the processing operation.

The composite key is typically generated from business-significant columns (e.g., order ID and customer ID) and is used for Kafka message partitioning and state management.

The data map contains all CSV columns except those used for the composite key, plus additional metadata fields added during processing.

  • Method Details

    • getCompositeKey

      public String getCompositeKey()
      Gets the composite key for this record.

      The composite key is typically formed by joining multiple business-significant CSV columns with underscores (e.g., "123_456" for order ID 123 and customer ID 456).

      Returns:
      the composite key (never null)

    • getData

      public Map<String,String> getData()
      Gets the processed data fields from the CSV row.

      This map contains all CSV columns except those used to generate the composite key, plus additional metadata fields added during processing (such as source filename and import timestamp).

      Returns:
      an immutable view of the data fields (never null)
